✅ Method 1: Use Valid_If (Best & Easy)
Go to your Phone column → set this formula in Valid_If:

COUNT(
  SELECT(
    YourTableName[Phone],
    [Phone] = [_THIS]
  )
) = 0
🔍 What it does:
Checks if the entered phone already exists
If found → ❌ Reject insert
If not found → ✅ Allow insert
  
🔥 Pro Tip (Dynamic message)
You can even make it dynamic:

"Duplicate: " & [_THIS] & " already exists"
  


⚠️ Important (for Edit case)
The above formula will block even editing the same row. So use this improved version:

COUNT(
  SELECT(
    YourTableName[Phone],
    AND(
      [Phone] = [_THIS],
      [_ROWNUMBER] <> [_THISROW].[_ROWNUMBER]
    )
  )
) = 0






  
